<text>When we first moved to the neighborhood in 2013 this was the type of place we thought we would eat at 2-3 times per week. Unfortunately the quality of the food has gotten worse at this Mom and Pop place. Basic items like carnitas, tamales and tacos are generally dry and over cooked. The owner is really one of the nicest guys ever - but the food lags the taste and quality of Tacko and Nicks Tacos. I really hope the quality improves, but so far the menu is stuck in time, over seasoned and often not the best in the area. They do allow for ordering ahead on several apps which is very convenient.</text>< Pics>

5< /Rating>
<Review>If you like those dripping greasy burritos with crappy meat - go to the MIssion.

If you like burritos that taste great and don't make you hate yourself, then hit up Canasta.

Likes:
1) Carne asada and pollo asada are both lean meat, grilled to order on a real grill - not some slab of hot metal that's greased up like a WWE wrestler.

2) All of their stuff is homemade.  And they ensure that it's all healthy - por ejemploo - the black beans don't have lard like most joints.  And they cook with heart healthy oils.

3)  Been going here for about 10 years now and I've tried to find a comparable burrito.  I can't.  And I don't like Pancho Villa/El Farolito grease pits.  I don't get those places.  Oh yea, people are wasted when they eat there.  Of course they think they're good.

4) They have habanero sauce!  Don't know why this isn't a staple?

5) Love the owner, super nice guy!  Always has a story to share.

Bads:
1) It's expensive

*this was pretty much copy/pasted from my yelp review</Review><Pics>None<//Pics>< resp>
None</resp>

<rate>5<//rate>< Text>
Yum!

Fully vegan impossible burger! Ordered via delivery though the location isn't bad to find and do a quick pickup. Packaged perfectly and delicious! Quick turn around from the restaurant which is excellent!

Exactly how I would like a fast food burger. Fairly priced and good quality.

Its always nice to have a vegan burger as an option and so glad this is becoming the new norm. Since I had it delivered, I warmed it up a bit more to get it extra hot which held up fantastically.

Would definitely order again if I needed a quick bite! Much try, with two different locations to choose from.</Text>

< text>
Funky Fries used to be better. They used to serve big crinkle-cut fries with loads of toppings, and it would fill a large standard clamshell container. Now they serve basic compressed potato starch shoestring fries in a little rectangle container with a handful of toppings for considerably more money. It's like they decided to go hipster for no good reason. East County establishments are supposed to serve tasty treats with Southern roots in big portions. I'm disappointed.</text>

<Name>Paul Scalone</Name>< Date>
1516421364442<//Date>
<Rate>4</Rate>< Review>
Bummed it took me so long to come here. I have known about them for quite a while as I used to drive by their original location in El Cajon on Washington. The buns are delicious, chewy, almost like a pretzel bun but lighter and not dry at all. The patties were cooked perfectly and their "funky sauce" is almost like a stone ground mustard base, very delicious if your into that, thankfully I am! The fries were equally delicious, sprinkled with a great seasoning. I had their traditional chocolate milkshake, it too was on point. They offer a wide array of frys that are pretty much a meal, like Buffalo fries, chilli fries, etc.. I will most certainly go back to try them at some point! Almost forgot to mention their over the top milkshakes stacked with cupcakes and other delicious nonsense!!< /Review>

114670773567409363259< /UserId.>
<Pictures>None</Pictures><response>None<//response>< Time>
1518651579535</Time>
<review>Funky Fries and Burgers has ridiculously good food in ridiculous proportions. I tried the Bacon Mac and Cheese Burger and a Cin-ful Shake. Like all Funky Burgers, the Bacon Mac and Cheese Burger has a hearty patty. The Mac and Cheese doesn't come just slopped on like at some restaurants. Instead, it comes contained in a fried shell that is about the same thickness as the patty. Think mozzarella stick in patty form, stuffed with mac and cheese. There is a generous amount of well-cooked bacon slabbed on, too. Not so crispy that it's brittle but not so soft that it's difficult to bite through, this bacon is made to be on a burger. The Cin-ful shake really is sinful. Icing coats the outside of this shake, with Cinnamon Toast Crunch and Cinnamon Rolls stuck to it. The shake itself is a delicious cinnamon blend topped with churros and a cinnamon bun. This is dessert and a drink in one. I can't imagine finishing a Funky Shake by myself... If you haven't tried Funky Fries, it's worth giving it a shot. I would readily say it's one of my top five favorite burger joints in San Diego.< /review></record></dataset><record>

< Name>
Connor Nelson< /Name>
<time>1562786845413</time><Rate>5</Rate>< Review>
The Cafe, was absolutely my favorite restaurant in town. The food was superb, the service top notch and not extremely expensive.
Table 57 retains most of those qualities, and improves. The fries, which were already great, are now better perfectly soft and crunchy at the same time, and seasoned incredibly well.
The interior is vastly different, the Cafe, previously, was very industrial with tasteful and artistic graffiti decorating the walls, making it highly memorable and standoutish.
Table 57 is the opposite. They went for a modern, clean, upscale look, that, to me comes off as uninspired and bland. It looks nice, but it's not any different than the usual fancy restaurant. But let's be honest, the decor is not the reason people go to restaurants. The food, retains the best parts of the Cafe and improves upon them.
Every item is handmade, from fresh ingredients, and the chefs seem to enjoy sourcing items specifically from the valley, and keeping things local which is great.
I had literally zero complaints about the food, nor the staff. It was entirely perfect.

In short, no table 57 isn't the imitating Cafe. It's just as good, if not better in most aspects. The staff are incredibly friendly and know what they're doing. Hands down, this is, once again, my favorite, and personal pick for the best restaurant in Visalia.<//Review>

< Review>
Had to edit my review. My second visit was not as awesome. The oatmeal was really soupy and it was instant. It wasn't served with the same stuff as the first time. <review>Went for breakfast with high expectations.  The menu is very small but they offer daily specials to change it up a bit. We ordered the daily omelet and an order of the tri tip and eggs. Food came quickly. Omelet was fine, nothing special with a price tag of $14. The tri tip and eggs (also $14) was not what we expected. It arrived in a bowl with a few cubes of meat swimming in a brown, thick sauce and eggs on the side. Menu said nothing of a sauce. Our personal situation and diet does not allow for gravys or sauces so the only thing we could personally eat was the eggs. The waitress never came to check on us after delivering the food. When it was time to bring the bill, she asked if there was something wrong with it since we had not touched it, we told her we didn't know it came in sauce and are not able to eat it. She took it away, left the bill and said sorry about that. Left $42 lighter and hungry with no warm feelings to return.

Two things would have made it better, the menu should include more details and we should have asked how it was prepared. Lesson learned.<//review>< pics>

<pictures>None<//pictures><review>Myself and my daughter stayed here while visiting family in feb 2021. It was our first trip since the pandemic and we felt so comfortable with the cleanliness of the room and the entire hotel. During a time of uncertainty this hotel staff gave us peace of mind that we were safe. The manager David and a member of his staff named Ciro really stood out in making us feel like family. David was very accommodating even before our trip had started. Ciro made us feel like family when we checked in. He put together the cutest welcome bag for my young daughter to lighten up the mood of why we had taken the trip (celebration of life ceremony for a family member was the main reason for our trip) As we would come and go off the property we would see staff sanitizing commonly touched places like the door handles, elevators, counter tops, bell carts, etc. They were also very good at enforcing masks. Our room was spacious and clean and had everything we needed for our stay. The property is gated and you need your key card to get in and out of the parking lot which I loved because you knew your car was in a safe parking lot. The front doors close at 7pm I believe and you need your key card to get in and out of the building which was another thing I really liked. The hotel is very close to Disney so I can imagine that being convenient when the parks open back up. David and his staff have gained a patron for life!< /review><response>{'time': 1614358060294, 'text': 'Thank you for the wonderful compliments and thank you for you business. < Rating>
5< /Rating>
< text>
I totally love this place it's so clean everything is decorated so nicely. I got the King suite. The bed was so comfy! It's a large room. When you first walk in you are in the living room area. Why a couch, chair, desk and a nice size TV mounted to the wall. The fridge and microwave are there as well. The decor in the walls are great.. The lighting in the bathroom was great. I know for women that's important when doing their make up.  Then as you pass the bathroom you get to the bedroom. Huge beautiful dresser and a King Bed. Huge windows with black out shades or close to it.
You can see the snow capped mountains. We saw fireworks from the room. It was NYE
Due to covid the place was very quiet. The bar and breakfast area was out of commission but that area was so nice. The pool and spa are open! Most hotels in this area don't let you use the spa or the pool due to covid.
Down by the garage there a small laundry room. Free of charge there are only two washers and two dryers. You can only get into the hotel if you are a guest so I think it makes it feel very safe. There's a small shop by the front desk for drinks and a small selection of snacks. The staff was friendly!! I wanted to post pictures but I'm having an issue with the memory in my phone. Maybe I can post pictures later.
I paid any $109 - $114 for the room with and $100 deposit.
I was able to charge thing to the room from the little shop by front desk and they'd deduct it from my deposit. That was convenient.
The location is great it's close to Disneyland and a bunch of restaurants. Cheesecake factory is close enough to walk. There a small starbucks, jersey mike's, the habit burger, Ono hawaiian, Luna grill, California fish grill and I believe a yogurt land. Across the street from there is 711 and a few other shops by the gas station. There a donut shop, pics place called EATalia and Magicland liquor store, laundromat. Hope you like this review. Even though the hotel is close to the freeway you can't hear a thing!!!</text>

< Review>
Stayed at the Suncoast Park while visiting Disneyland for a few days. The staff was helpful,friendly, and courteous, the rooms and public areas bright and clean, and the rooms reasonably priced. My room had two queen beds, a refrigerator, microwave, and a small safe located in the bathroom. The location was perfect for visiting Disneyland and other local attractions. The Garden Walk Mall and Entertainment Center is a half-mile away and worth a visit. Disneyland was a pleasant 15 minute stroll away and the hotel is easily accessed by freeway. The have a nice modestly priced breakfast buffet and a great pool and patio area. There is a Pub type bar and I believe they serve dinner in the evenings. There is plenty of indoor and outdoor parking for a small additional cost. I deducted one star only because our room faced a very busy freeway which made the room a little noisy and sleep difficult. I would suggest requesting a room facing away from the freeway. Would happily return again.<//Review>

I had a horrible time at this hospital. Due to their negligent acupuncture my elderly dog suffered a negative reaction. She was in severe pain and had to be taken to the emergency. Also they overcharged us and tried to push us for more tests.

Dr. Chi-Shan does not understand what is being said to her, but both Dr. Wentworth and Dr. Chi-Shan Hsu gave me bad medical advice about not giving my dog the proper medicine from the emergency clinic. They specifically told me not to give my dog  prednisolone and  gabapentin as these drugs did nothing.

They offered to come euthanize my dog for 400, when everyone thinks it's pretty despicable that they made my dog ill, and did not think to come for free afterwards to check.

After many days suffering, and being lied to, my dog had to be euthanized.

They overcharged me an included exam fee of 79.00 and an unnecessary urinalysis which was supposed to detect what stage kidney my dog had, but which actually had to be a blood test.

Dr. Chi-Shan also tries to tack on as many unnecessary charges which may or may not be beneficial. I was tired and in a hurry to leave so I had someone else sign for me. They also had to test my dogs blood twice. Since it was suggested that my dog may have twisted her spine in a struggle, I think it was caused there.  I carried her out so I did not check to see if she could walk. At home she no longer was able to walk.

Also all veterinarians advised me no surgery, but if you need surgery do it right away. Don't believe it is healing from the acupuncture. I lost my dogs life because I did not give correct medicine and did not do surgery right when it happened.

UPDATE:
Let me be clear that Dr. Kathy Wentworth knowingly gave bad medical advice that made my dog suffer more greatly during the last days of her life. It is only what someone truly psychopathic would do.
She is a cold-hearted person who seemed nice the first time I met her, but someone who would sink this low is pretty despicable.
Dr. Chi-Shan was out helping other patients and made us wait while our dog was hooked up to the electro-acupuncture machine . She was not overseeing the process. I found out from another acupuncturist that for elder dogs they can be sensitive and it was not a good idea to use electro-acupuncture or so many needles as it overstimulates and can be detrimental.
If they had done the right thing and tried to help fix the problem they created and made worse I would have been more forgiving. But, they made everything worse at the end of my dog's life.</Text>

<Rate>5< /Rate><review>So many great things to say about this theater! First off, they have ample free parking which is always a great start. It's also great that they have 18 screens at this theater which means they have tons of showtimes and they show lots of films, even some of the indie flicks.

Del Amo also has an IMAX and a Dolby screen which are both fantastic quality. It's always great seeing action films and movies with great music/sound on these screens. I'm personally not a fan of 3D, but they also show several films in this format as well.

This theater is also attached to one of my favorite mall, so there's always tons to do before and after a good movie, from great shopping to excellent food options.

Lastly I love that you can reserve your seat ahead of time. This creates less stress and you can arrive confidently knowing your seat already.</review>< Pictures>

<userid>106247541248001088593< /userid><username>Jay Torres</username><date>1504945398266<//date><Rate>4</Rate>< review>
Took in a movie at 12:30 pm on a Friday afternoon and it wasn't crowded at all. It's been a while since I've been here and I forgot that I had a $10 credit on my Stubs membership so it came in handy as I saved $10 on 2 tickets which knocked down the price to $15 and some change! They've also got some new offerings in food and I tried a small chicken and waffle sandwich with honey mustard sauce and some curly fries and it was pretty good. It also came with a soft chocolate chip cookie which satisfied my sweet tooth all at just over $12! They could do better with the Stubs membership by offering more than having to spend $100 to get $10 off your tix or concessions, maybe giving you a break at every $50 spent. The free upgrade feature is okay where you're able to upgrade from a regular to a large but the sodas are overpriced to begin with at $5.70 or so they should lower that price by at least a dollar. Overall I enjoyed the experience...</review>

I decided to rent a theater for my family and had a great experience. I spent $300 to chose one of the premium movies and I was able to invite upto 20 people.  During covid-19, renting a theater for the family was awesome. My group had an age range from 7 to 70yrs old and we all had a great time. I'll be doing it again for sure.

This theater was very clean, the sound and picture was great. This is a nice AMC. Easy parking.

I would suggest paying for the AMC stubs premium if you are going to rent a theater. Be sure to check out the perks.<//Text>
